 Berger Paints Nigeria Plc, one of Nigeriaâ€™s paint manufacturing companies, has announced the appointment of Mr. Adeyemi Adetomiwa formerly Chief Operating Officer of the Company as Acting Managing Director/Chief Executive Officer. The new appointment came as a result of the retirement of Mr. Anjan Sircar as MD/CEO of the company. The appointment of Adeyemi takes effect on January 4, 2022. Adeyemi , according to a statement from Berger Paints, brings on board almost three decades of management experience in the manufacturing industry. He is a Certified Environmental Scientist (National Registry of Environmental Professionals, U S A) and holds a B.Tech Degree in Chemistry from the Ladoke Akintola University of Technology, Ogbomosho. He joined the services of CAP Plc as an Assistant Production Manager in 2001 and worked in various capacities including Process Support Manager, Planning Manager, and Plant Manager. Between 2011 and 2018, he also served as the Technical Operations Manager (Acting), Quality Manager, Health, Safety, Environment, and Quality Manager. He joined Berger Paints Nigeria Plc in 2019 as Chief Operating Officer. 